<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Lead-gen reality at gyms in 2026</span><h2 class="h2">The honest picture</h2><ul class="ul"><li><strong>Lead costs are rising.</strong> Meta CPMs up 30-50% over 24 months; Google Ads CPC up across most local fitness markets.</li><li><strong>Lead quality is variable.</strong> Cheap leads (lead-form ads, lead magnets) often convert poorly; expensive leads (organic from website) often convert well.</li><li><strong>What you do AFTER the lead matters more than the channel.</strong> AI agent lead nurture (60-second response + conversational qualification) typically converts 30-45% of leads to tour attendance vs 5-15% with no follow-up.</li><li><strong>Most gyms don't measure cost-per-acquired-member correctly.</strong> CAC = total marketing spend ÷ new members acquired, NOT cost per lead × conversion. The math gets distorted at the lead stage.</li></ul></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Cost per lead by channel</span><h2 class="h2">May 2026 benchmarks</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table class="t"><thead><tr><th>Channel</th><th>Typical cost per lead</th><th>Lead-to-tour conversion</th><th>Effective cost per tour</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Meta lead form ads</td><td>\$8-\$25</td><td>15-25%</td><td>\$45-\$170</td></tr><tr><td>Meta conversion ads (to website)</td><td>\$15-\$45</td><td>25-35%</td><td>\$50-\$180</td></tr><tr><td>Google Search ads (local intent)</td><td>\$30-\$80</td><td>30-45%</td><td>\$70-\$270</td></tr><tr><td>Google Business Profile (organic)</td><td>\$0</td><td>40-55%</td><td>\$0 + staff time</td></tr><tr><td>Member referral</td><td>\$0-\$50 (referral reward)</td><td>55-70%</td><td>\$0-\$80</td></tr><tr><td>Local partnership referrals</td><td>\$0-\$25 avg</td><td>45-60%</td><td>\$0-\$55</td></tr><tr><td>Walk-in (street + signage)</td><td>\$0</td><td>35-50%</td><td>\$0</td></tr><tr><td>Past member win-back</td><td>\$0</td><td>25-40%</td><td>\$0</td></tr></tbody></table></div><div class="callout"><p>The biggest lever isn't the channel, it's whether you have AI-agent lead nurture on the back end. The same paid social lead converts at 5-15% with no follow-up vs 30-45% with AI agent nurture. The economics shift dramatically. See <a href="/how-to-use-ai-for-gym-lead-nurture" style="color:#00C853;">how to use AI for gym lead nurture</a>.</p></div></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Channel-by-channel guide</span><h2 class="h2">What to do at each</h2><h3 class="h3">Meta (Facebook, Instagram)</h3><p class="body">Highest volume of paid leads at most operators. Tight geo-targeting (1-3 mi radius), member-faced creative, constant creative iteration. Use Meta lead-form ads OR conversion-to-website ads depending on follow-up workflow.</p><h3 class="h3">Google Search Ads</h3><p class="body">Lower volume than Meta but higher commercial intent. Targets: "[city] gym", "[city] CrossFit", "[city] yoga studio", brand-name competitor terms. Expensive per click but converts well.</p><h3 class="h3">Google Business Profile (free)</h3><p class="body">Underrated. Most gyms have incomplete/stale GBP. Active management, weekly photos, prompt review responses, complete service listings, drives free, high-converting inbound. Should be a baseline; isn't at most operators.</p><h3 class="h3">Member referrals</h3><p class="body">Highest ROI channel. Structured program with simple reward (give-a-month/get-a-month is the classic). Active solicitation ("who do you know?") at appropriate moments. See <a href="/gym-referral-program" style="color:#00C853;">gym referral program guide</a>.</p><h3 class="h3">Local partnerships</h3><p class="body">Adjacent local businesses (juice bars, athleisure, physiotherapy, salons). Mutual referral structures. Slow-build channel; compounds over 12-24 months.</p><h3 class="h3">Past member win-back</h3><p class="body">Most operators ignore. Lapsed members who churned 3-12 months ago often re-engage with appropriate outreach. AI agent can run this systematically.</p></div></section>
<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">The AI agent layer</span><h2 class="h2">Why this changes the lead-gen math</h2><p class="body">The conversion rates in the channel table above assume AI agent lead nurture. Without it, expect 30-50% lower conversion across every paid channel. The math:</p><ul class="ul"><li>Paid social: \$25 cost per lead × 15% manual conversion = \$170 per tour</li><li>Paid social: \$25 cost per lead × 35% AI-agent conversion = \$70 per tour</li><li>Same lead, same paid spend, 60%+ cost-per-tour reduction</li></ul><p class="body"><a href="https://fitagentic.ai" style="color:#00C853;">fitagentic.ai</a> is the platform purpose-built for fitness lead-nurture agents. Multi-unit operator pricing; integrates with major gym CRMs.</p></div></section>

